ould read), indicating a hypothetical situation. Person A's question must match with 'What would you read if you had more time' to invite this type of imagined scenario.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 4,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"B1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Medium\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If she studied more regularly, she might improve her grades.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Do you think she will improve her grades if she studies more regularly?\",\n          \"Do you think she would improve her grades if she studied more regularly?\",\n          \"Do you think she would have improved her grades if she had studied more regularly?\",\n          \"Do you think she improved her grades if she studied more regularly?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Do you think she would improve her grades if she studied more regularly?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a second conditional (If she studied\u2026she might improve), indicating a hypothetical present situation. Person A's question must also use second conditional: 'would improve if she studied more regularly.'\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 5,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"B1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Medium\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If he worked harder, he could get a promotion.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Do you think he will get a promotion if he works harder?\",\n          \"Do you think he would get a promotion if he worked harder?\",\n          \"D