rst conditional context.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 14,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"B2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Medium\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If the customer had placed the order earlier, we could have delivered it on time.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Could we have delivered it on time if the customer had placed the order earlier?\",\n          \"Will we deliver it on time if the customer places the order earlier?\",\n          \"Would we deliver it on time if the customer placed the order earlier?\",\n          \"Did we deliver it on time if the customer had placed the order earlier?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Could we have delivered it on time if the customer had placed the order earlier?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a third conditional (If the customer had placed\u2026we could have delivered), referring to an unreal past event. Person A's question must match with 'Could we have delivered\u2026if the customer had placed,' the standard third conditional question form.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 16,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"B2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Medium\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If the teacher had explained the concept earlier, the students would have understood it better.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Could the students have understood the concept better if the teacher had explained it earlier?\",\n          \"Can the students understand the concept better if the teacher explains it earlier?\",\n          \"Would the students understand the concept better if the teacher explains it earlier?\",\n          \"Did the students understand the concept better if the teacher had explained it earlier?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Could the students have understood the concept better if the teacher had explained it earlier?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a third conditional (if the teacher had explained\u2026the students would have understood), referring to an unreal past event. Person A's question must match with 'Could the students have understood\u2026if the teacher had explained,' the standard third conditional question form.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"hard\": [\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 16,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: Had the project been managed more efficiently, the team would have met the deadline.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"What would have happened if the project had been managed more efficiently?\",\n          \"What will happen if the project is managed more efficiently?\",\n          \"What would happen if the project is managed more efficiently now?\",\n          \"What happened when the project was managed more efficiently?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"What would have happened if the project had been managed more efficiently?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a third conditional (Had the project been\u2026the team would have). Person A's question must use 'What would have happened if the project had been,' which matches this third conditional structure.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 17,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If I were you, I would apologize to her immediately and make amends.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"What would you do if you were me?\",\n          \"What will you do if you are me?\",\n          \"What would you have done if you were me?\",\n          \"What did you do when you were me?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"What would you do if you were me?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a first conditional inversion (If I were you\u2026I would apologize). Person A's question must use 'What would you do if you were me,' which correctly matches the first conditional structure.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 18,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: Were the company to invest more in research and development, it would likely increase its market share.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"What would happen to the company's market share if it were to invest more in R&D?\",\n          \"What will happen to the company's market share if it invests more in R&D?\",\n          \"What would have happened to the company's market share if it had invested more in R&D?\",\n          \"What happened to the company's market share when it invested more in R&D?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"What would happen to the company's market share if it were to invest more in R&D?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a formal second conditional inversion (Were the company to invest\u2026would likely increase). Person A's question must use 'What would happen to the company's market share if it were to invest more in R&D,' which correctly matches the hypothetical second conditional.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 19,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: If she had studied harder for the exam, she would have passed with flying colors.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Would she have passed the exam if she had studied harder?\",\n          \"Will she pass the exam if she studies harder?\",\n          \"Would she pass the exam if she studies harder now?\",\n          \"Did she pass the exam when she studied harder?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Would she have passed the exam if she had studied harder?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a mixed conditional (If she had studied harder\u2026she would have passed). Person A's question must use 'Would she have passed the exam if she had studied harder,' which is the correct mixed conditional interrogative.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 21,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C1\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: Were the company to invest more in research and development, it would likely increase its market share.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"What would happen to the company's market share if it invested more in R&D?\",\n          \"What will happen to the company's market share if it invests more in R&D?\",\n          \"What would have happened to the company's market share if it had invested more in R&D?\",\n          \"What happened to the company's market share when it invested more in R&D?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"What would happen to the company's market share if it invested more in R&D?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B uses a formal second conditional inversion (Were the company to invest\u2026would increase). Person A's question must use 'What would happen if the company invested more,' which correctly matches the hypothetical second conditional.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 21,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: It might, especially if the speaker uses clear examples and avoids jargon.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Will the lecture be accessible to students who are new to the subject?\",\n          \"Would the lecture be accessible to students who had been new to the subject?\",\n          \"Was the lecture accessible to students who had been new to the subject?\",\n          \"Has the lecture been accessible to students who were new to the subject?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Will the lecture be accessible to students who are new to the subject?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B predicts a future possibility using 'might,' responding to a forward-looking question. Person A's question uses 'Will\u2026be accessible,' which correctly invites this kind of conditional future evaluation.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 22,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: It could, especially if you allocate sufficient time for practice and review.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Will studying for two hours daily improve vocabulary acquisition?\",\n          \"Did studying for two hours daily improve vocabulary acquisition?\",\n          \"Has studying for two hours daily improved vocabulary acquisition?\",\n          \"Is studying for two hours daily improving vocabulary acquisition?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Will studying for two hours daily improve vocabulary acquisition?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B gives a conditional future prediction using 'could,' responding to a forward-looking question about potential improvement. Person A's question uses 'Will\u2026improve,' which correctly invites this kind of evaluative conditional response.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 23,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: It may, especially if the participants actively engage in discussions.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Will the workshop enhance critical thinking skills?\",\n          \"Would the workshop enhance critical thinking skills?\",\n          \"Did the workshop enhance critical thinking skills?\",\n          \"Has the workshop enhanced critical thinking skills?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Will the workshop enhance critical thinking skills?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B predicts a future possibility using 'may,' responding to a forward-looking question. Person A's question uses 'Will\u2026enhance,' which correctly invites this kind of conditional future evaluation.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 24,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: It should, especially if the instructor provides clear learning objectives.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Will the course improve learning outcomes?\",\n          \"Would the course improve learning outcomes?\",\n          \"Did the course improve learning outcomes?\",\n          \"Has the course improved learning outcomes?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Will the course improve learning outcomes?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B gives a strong recommendation using 'should,' responding to a forward-looking question. Person A's question uses 'Will\u2026improve,' which correctly invites this kind of evaluative conditional response.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"question_number\": 25,\n        \"topic\": \"English Grammar\\n\",\n        \"subtopic\": \"Conditioansl\",\n        \"target_cefr\": \"C2\",\n        \"target_difficulty\": \"Hard\",\n        \"instruction\": \"Choose the correct option that completes the following conversation.\",\n        \"question\": \"Person A: _______________________<br>Person B: It would, especially if the team members collaborate effectively.\",\n        \"options\": [\n          \"Will the project succeed?\",\n          \"Would the project succeed?\",\n          \"Did the project succeed?\",\n          \"Has the project succeeded?\"\n        ],\n        \"correct_answer\": \"Will the project succeed?\",\n        \"explanation\": \"Person B gives a hypothetical pre